[{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":23,"sectionNumber":1,"value":" "},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":1,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"You are righteous, Yahweh, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":1,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"when I contend with you; "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":1,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"yet I would like to reason the cause with you. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":1,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"Why does the way of the wicked prosper? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":1,"sectionNumber":5,"value":"Why are they all at ease who deal very treacherously? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":2,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"You have planted them. Yes, they have taken root. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":2,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"They grow. Yes, they produce fruit. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":2,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"You are near in their mouth, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":2,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"and far from their heart. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":3,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"But you, Yahweh, know me. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":3,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"You see me, and test my heart toward you. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":3,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"Pull them out like sheep for the slaughter, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":3,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"and prepare them for the day of slaughter. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":4,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"How long will the land mourn, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":4,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"and the herbs of the whole country wither? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":4,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"Because of the wickedness of those who dwell therein, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":4,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"the animals and birds are consumed; "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":4,"sectionNumber":5,"value":"because they said, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":4,"sectionNumber":6,"value":"“He won’t see our latter end.” "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":5,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"“If you have run with the footmen, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":5,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"and they have wearied you, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":5,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"then how can you contend with horses? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":5,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"Though in a land of peace you are secure, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":5,"sectionNumber":5,"value":"yet how will you do in the pride of the Jordan? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":6,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"For even your brothers, and the house of your father, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":6,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"even they have dealt treacherously with you! "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":6,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"Even they have cried aloud after you! "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":6,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"Don’t believe them, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":6,"sectionNumber":5,"value":"though they speak beautiful words to you. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"stanza end"},{"type":"stanza start"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":6,"sectionNumber":6,"value":" "},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":7,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"“I have forsaken my house. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":7,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"I have cast off my heritage. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":7,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"I have given the dearly beloved of my soul into the hand of her enemies. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":8,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"My heritage has become to me as a lion in the forest. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":8,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"She has uttered her voice against me. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":8,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"Therefore I have hated her. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":9,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"Is my heritage to me as a speckled bird of prey? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":9,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"Are the birds of prey against her all around? "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":9,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"Go, assemble all the animals of the field. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":9,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"Bring them to devour. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":10,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"Many shepherds have destroyed my vineyard. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":10,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"They have trodden my portion under foot. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":10,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"They have made my pleasant portion a desolate wilderness. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":11,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"They have made it a desolation. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":11,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"It mourns to me, being desolate. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":11,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"The whole land is made desolate, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":11,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"because no one cares. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":12,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"Destroyers have come on all the bare heights in the wilderness; "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":12,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"for the sword of Yahweh devours from the one end of the land even to the other end of the land. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":12,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"No flesh has peace. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":13,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"They have sown wheat, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":13,"sectionNumber":2,"value":"and have reaped thorns. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":13,"sectionNumber":3,"value":"They have exhausted themselves, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":13,"sectionNumber":4,"value":"and profit nothing. "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":13,"sectionNumber":5,"value":"You will be ashamed of your fruits, "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"line text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":13,"sectionNumber":6,"value":"because of Yahweh’s fierce anger.” "},{"type":"line break"},{"type":"stanza end"},{"type":"stanza start"},{"type":"stanza end"},{"type":"paragraph start"},{"type":"paragraph text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":14,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"Yahweh says, “Concerning all my evil neighbors, who touch the inheritance which I have caused my people Israel to inherit: Behold, I will pluck them up from off their land, and will pluck up the house of Judah from among them.  "},{"type":"paragraph text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":15,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"It will happen that after I have plucked them up, I will return and have compassion on them. I will bring them again, every man to his heritage, and every man to his land.  "},{"type":"paragraph text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":16,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"It will happen, if they will diligently learn the ways of my people, to swear by my name, ‘As Yahweh lives;’ even as they taught my people to swear by Baal, then they will be built up in the middle of my people.  "},{"type":"paragraph text","chapterNumber":12,"verseNumber":17,"sectionNumber":1,"value":"But if they will not hear, then I will pluck up that nation, plucking up and destroying it,” says Yahweh. "},{"type":"paragraph end"},{"type":"paragraph start"}]